<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAY 94 / Strike to close Greek airports
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ATHENS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Greek air traffic controllers announced a 48-hour strike beginning today
that would paralyse airports and create chaos for thousands of fans arriving
for the European Champion's Cup football final tomorrow evening. A civil
aviation union official, Mr Dimitris Petrissis, said yesterday the walk-out
was called to protest against legislation under debate in parliament placing
civil aviation employees under the control of local governors. About 300
extra flights were scheduled to arrive in the next 24 hours from Spain and
Italy carrying fans for the AC Milan-Barcelona game.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GRZ  Greece, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
