<HEADLINE>
FT  16 MAY 94 / International Company News: Recovery at Tabacalera
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Tabacalera, the partly-privatised Spanish tobacco monopoly, saw earnings
recover in the first quarter of the year after a sharp setback in 1993,
writes David White in Madrid.
Pre-tax profits were 17 per cent higher at just under Pta4bn (Dollars 29m).
Net sales reversed last year's trend to increase by 9 per cent to Pta140bn
in the three months.
</TEXT>
