<HEADLINE>
FT  16 MAY 94 / International Company News: Hollinger ahead in first quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hollinger, the Canadian holding company of Mr Conrad Black, says its
publishing properties are improving with a significant recovery in
advertising, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
First-quarter profit was CDollars 12.6m (USDollars 9.1m) or 22 cents a
share, against CDollars 13.7m or 20 cents a year earlier.
Hollinger owns newspaper holdings in North America, Australia and Israel,
and 66.2 per cent of the Telegraph Group in the UK.
</TEXT>
