something that Rupert Murdoch certainly cannot boast
For Judge Breyer was married in 1969 to the former Joanna Hare, which makes
him the brother-in-law of Viscount Blakenham, the current Pearson chairman,
and nephew-in-law of the Hon Alan Hare, ex-chairman of the FT. In a story we
could never use last summer, because Breyer lost out to Ruth Bader Ginsburg
for the last Court vacancy, the family was quizzed about its in-law, but
remained discreet. 'He likes a spot of good claret,' one of them said, in
itself a pretty fair recommendation for the world's most famous judicial
